One man who was unfortunate to miss out on attending the opening ceremony after catching coronavirus is theTony Estanguet, president of the Paris 2024 Organizing Committee. Since he wasn't able to come to Beijing, he sent his best wishes for the Games in an exclusive interview with Sports Scene anchor Wang Dong. The former Olympic champion and former IOC member said it's very important for Paris to observe and learn from Beijing's preparations as they get ready to host the Games in two years.